Step 1: Identify the two numbers needed for the ratio:  
• Net Profit = 1903401.82  
• Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities = -862455.97  

Step 2: Calculate the ratio using the formula:  
  Operating Cash Flow to Net Income Ratio = (Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities) / (Net Profit)

Step 3: Substitute the values:  
  = (-862455.97) / (1903401.82)  
  ≈ -0.4527

Step 4: Round the ratio to two decimal places:  
  ≈ -0.45

Thus, the Operating Cash Flow to Net Income Ratio is -0.45.
